2 SECTION 14. IC 36-8-4-5, AS AMENDED BY P.L.66-2020,
3 SECTION 1, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
4 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 5. (a) The following definitions apply
5 throughout this section:
6 (1) "Firefighter" means a current or former firefighter.
7 (2) "Police officer" means a current or former police officer.
8 (a) (b) A city shall pay for the care of a police officer or firefighter
9 who suffers an injury while performing the person's duty or while the
10 person is on duty or who contracts illness caused by the performance
11 of the person's duty, including an injury or illness that results in a
12 disability or death presumed incurred in the line of duty under
13 IC 5-10-13. This care includes:
14 (1) medical and surgical care;
15 (2) medicines and laboratory, curative, and palliative agents and
16 means;
17 (3) X-ray, diagnostic, and therapeutic service, including during
18 the recovery period; and
19 (4) hospital and special nursing care if the physician or surgeon
20 in charge considers it necessary for proper recovery.
21 (b) (c) Expenditures required by subsection (a) (b) shall be paid
22 from the general fund of the city.
23 (c) (d) A city that has paid for the care of a police officer or
24 firefighter under subsection (a) (b) has a cause of action for
25 reimbursement of the amount paid under subsection (a) (b) against any
26 third party against whom the police officer or firefighter has a cause of
27 action for an injury sustained because of or an illness caused by the
28 third party. The city's cause of action under this subsection is in
29 addition to, and not in lieu of, the cause of action of the police officer
30 or firefighter against the third party.
31 (e) The medical benefits under this section are independent and
32 distinct from any medical benefits that are available under IC 22-3.
33 A police officer or firefighter may recover medical benefits under
34 this section without first pursuing a claim for medical benefits
35 under IC 22-3. If a police officer or firefighter pursues a claim for
36 medical benefits under IC 22-3 and the claim is withdrawn or
37 denied, the police officer or firefighter is not precluded from
38 recovering medical benefits under this section.
